<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jonahb55/48/194474_2.png" class="avatar"> jonahb55:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Also make sure to carefully follow the <a href="https://docs.advantagescope.org/more-features/gltf-convert/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">instructions </a> for exporting as a glb file, rather than gltf.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>To be more precise, I think you need to export your robot to 3 glb files.  You are have two components in your json file, you need to seperate the two components (like an arm or whatever) from your cad and export them as glb files.</p>
<p>When you finish, you should have these files:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">config.json
model.glb
model_0.glb
model_1.glb
</code></pre>
<p>where <code>model_0.glb</code> and <code>model_1</code> are the 3d models of your movable components, and <code>model.glb</code> is the 3d model of your drivetrain.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2024-10-11T00:52:34.483Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":109,"readers_count":108,"score":41.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":472762,"topic_slug":"issues-adding-custom-assets-to-advantage-scope","display_username":"sam liu","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60033,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"CE Student @ UWaterloo | 5516 Alum "},"post_url":"/t/issues-adding-custom-assets-to-advantage-scope/472762/6","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3433517,"name":"Jonah Bonner","username":"jonahb55","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jonahb55/{size}/194474_2.png","created_at":"2024-10-11T02:38:07.122Z","cooked":"<p>glTF has two formats: “.gltf” is for the text representation and “.glb” is for the binary version. From the docs:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Note that AdvantageScope uses the binary form (.glb), which includes all resources in a single file, rather than the pure JSON form (.gltf).</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The main issue is that you want the model file to be named “model.glb” rather than using the name of the asset. And as pointed out above, if you define multiple components those should be in separate files. If you encounter any issues with that setup, it would be helpful if you can send a copy of the asset files to help with debugging.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2024-10-11T02:38:07.122Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":102,"readers_count":101,"score":50.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":472762,"topic_slug":"issues-adding-custom-assets-to-advantage-scope","display_username":"Jonah Bonner","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":61162,"username":"PanicLemming","name":null,"avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/paniclemming/{size}/234749_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44471,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6328M/WPILib"},"post_url":"/t/issues-adding-custom-assets-to-advantage-scope/472762/7","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3565768,"name":"Maxwell Tan","username":"maxtan0626","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/b5a626/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-23T03:03:45.322Z","cooked":"<p>Hey, I’m having the same issue where my model doesn’t show up.